maml:description.maml:para: Retrieves Time Entries from ConnectWise Manage.
Retrieves Time Entries from ConnectWise Manage. Can specify to return only entries for Member(s) of Argreement Id.
Agreement Id Number (use Get-CwmAgreement to obtain them)
Authstring created with Get-CwmAuthString, will default to $global:CwAuthString
Agreement Id Number (use Get-CwmAgreement to obtain them)
Authstring created with Get-CwmAuthString, will default to $global:CwAuthString

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- Example 1 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Get-CwmTimeEntries -Member 'tstark','bbanner'

dev:remarks.maml:para: Returns first 1000 Time Entries for users tstark and bbanner.

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- Example 2 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> $Agreement = Get-CwmAgreement 1 PS C:\> $Agreement | Get-CwmTimeEntries -Member 'tstark','bbanner' -PageSize 10

dev:remarks.maml:para: Returns first 10 Time Entries for users tstark and bbanner applied towards any agreement for Company with Id of 1.

maml:description.maml:para: Underlying Cmdlet used to create all api calls to ConnectWise Manage.
Underlying Cmdlet used to create all api calls to ConnectWise Manage. Can be used for API calls lacking a supporting Cmdlet.

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- Example 1 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Invoke-CwmApiCall -Uri https://example.connectwise.com/v4_6_release/apis/3.0/service/tickets -Method 'GET'

dev:remarks.maml:para: Returns the first 25 (default pagesize for api calls) service tickets.

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- Example 2 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Invoke-CwmApiCall -Uri https://example.connectwise.com/v4_6_release/apis/3.0/service/tickets -Method 'GET' -QueryParams @{ 'pageSize' = 10 } -QueryParams = @{ 'company/name' = 'My Example Company" }

dev:remarks.maml:para: Returns the first 10 service tickets for My Example Company.

maml:description.maml:para: Creates base64 string needed for APi Call Authorization Token.
Creates base64 string needed for APi Call Authorization Token. Value can be passed to other other cmdlets, but is also stored in global variable CwAuthString

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- Example 1 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> $AuthString = New-CwmAuthString -CwCompany 'mycompany' -CwPublicKey 'mypublickey' -CwPrivateKey 'myprivatekey' PS C:\> $Companies = Get-CwmCompany -AuthString $AuthString

dev:remarks.maml:para: Creates AuthString and uses it to query all Companies.
